<h2><span data-preserver-spaces="true">Usual causes of hair fall</span></h2>


<h3><span data-preserver-spaces="true">Hereditary factors</span></h3>


<p><span data-preserver-spaces="true">Genetics has a key role in deciding whether you will suffer from premature hair fall. However, with homeopathy medicine for hair fall, you can maintain good hair health despite genetic disadvantages.</span></p>


<h3><span data-preserver-spaces="true">Hormonal imbalance</span></h3>


<p><span data-preserver-spaces="true">Hormonal changes are also a major cause of why your hair may start thinning at a young age. Note that there are two phases of hair growth; the first one is anagen (growth phase), and the second is telogen (resting phase). Due to hormonal imbalances, the growth phase becomes shorter, and the resting phase gets stretched.�</span></p>


<p><span data-preserver-spaces="true">Secretion of the hormone also gets affected by other factors such as stress, emotional turbulence, medical condition, and more. All these can lead to premature hair fall.�</span></p>


<h3><span data-preserver-spaces="true">Lack of sufficient nutrition</span></h3>


<p><span data-preserver-spaces="true">If your body doesn�t get the nutrients it requires for natural growth, it can lead to hair loss. Remember, protein plays a key role in developing your hair strands. So, if your body doesn�t get the required amount of protein, it will affect the growth of your hair. Other nutrients that play key roles in stimulating hair growth and follicles include vitamins like folic acid (B9), biotin (B7), and multiple minerals.</span></p>


<h3><span data-preserver-spaces="true">Hairstyles</span></h3>


<p><span data-preserver-spaces="true">Following a hairstyle that puts extra pressure or creates tension in your hair strands can lead to gradual loss of hair.</span></p>


